## 6. Test Schedule / Milestone
- Test Planning: 2026-07-14 to 2026-07-18
- Script Development: 2026-07-19 to 2026-07-28
- Environment Setup: 2026-07-19 to 2026-07-21
- Test Execution: 2026-07-22 to 2026-07-29
- Regression & Reporting: 2026-07-30 to 2026-08-02
- Release Readiness: 2026-08-03
- Core QA Resources: 2 Automation Engineers, 1 Manual QA, 1 Performance Engineer, 1 Security Analyst

---

## 7. Assumptions
- Test environments and data will be available as scheduled.
- All tools (Playwright, PyTest, JMeter, OWASP ZAP, tcconfig) are licensed and accessible.
- Upstream and downstream systems are stable for integration testing.
- Team members have required skills and access.

---

## 8. Risks and Mitigations
| Risk ID | Description | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation Action | Owner |
|---------|-------------|--------|------------|-------------------|-------|
| R1 | Dynamic database connection drops during test runs | High | Medium | Implement retry logic and DB health checks in PyTest suites | QA Lead |
| R2 | SLA clock breaches under peak load | High | Medium | Use JMeter to simulate peak loads and tune system thresholds | Perf Eng |
| R3 | UI element selectors change frequently | Medium | High | Use resilient Playwright locators and nightly smoke runs | Automation Eng |
| R4 | Security scan false positives delay release | Medium | Medium | Pre-validate findings with OWASP ZAP and triage with Security | Security Analyst |
| R5 | Network throttling not reflecting real-world latency | Medium | Medium | Calibrate tcconfig profiles with production metrics | QA Lead |

